---
description: Security guardrails
alwaysApply: true
---
Transport layer security (TLS) 1.3 in production.
At rest encryption with advanced encryption standard (AES) 256 where the cloud offers it.
Authentication uses JSON web token (JWT) access plus refresh.
Never invent cryptography. Never return secrets in responses.
Mask tokens and secrets in logs.
Role based access control (RBAC) on server then attribute based access control (ABAC) for vessel scope.
Cross site request forgery (CSRF) protection on browser flows.
Personally identifiable information (PII) must not be logged.
Error shape is { code  message  traceId }.
Security tests must pass before merging.
